WEBVTT

00:08.342 --> 00:10.333
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

00:27.278 --> 00:29.018
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

00:30.364 --> 00:31.979
[THUNDER CRASHING]

00:54.805 --> 00:56.136
You found me.

00:58.059 --> 00:59.595
You didn't make it easy.

01:00.561 --> 01:02.267
I know I didn't.

01:03.356 --> 01:05.438
I needed space.

01:05.858 --> 01:06.893
To think.

01:07.109 --> 01:08.690
How's that working out for you?

01:12.782 --> 01:14.738
Still thinking.

01:17.954 --> 01:19.990
Yeah, me too.

01:20.957 --> 01:24.324
In fact,
I can't escape a single fucking thought...

01:24.543 --> 01:27.000
...space or no space.

01:28.047 --> 01:29.503
Why'd you come here, Jason?

01:29.715 --> 01:32.957
I came because I knew you'd ask
that fucking question.

01:33.135 --> 01:36.673
That you'd act like I must've been crazy...

01:36.889 --> 01:40.097
...thinking there was something,
anything between us.

01:40.309 --> 01:42.766
That you'd play the whole lone rider...

01:42.979 --> 01:47.814
..."l'm an island, I don't need shit
from anybody" thing that you do.

01:48.818 --> 01:51.355
I came because I fucking knew you'd do it.

01:52.446 --> 01:58.612
But that if it was true, you wouldn't
have to get that far away from me to think.

02:07.128 --> 02:11.212
So, what about Violet?

02:17.888 --> 02:19.298
I'm crazy about her.

02:22.476 --> 02:23.511
Hm.

02:24.770 --> 02:26.726
[JASON GRUNTS]

02:30.192 --> 02:32.057
But I can't get you out of my head.

02:34.697 --> 02:36.733
You probably hear that a lot, don't you?

02:37.366 --> 02:39.322
For a thousand years.

02:39.660 --> 02:42.527
Only twice have I felt it in return.

03:01.390 --> 03:02.425
[JASON GRUNTING]

03:15.738 --> 03:17.820
[GRUNTING]

03:19.950 --> 03:21.941
[BOTH PANTING]

04:12.378 --> 04:13.584
[JASON MOANS]

04:17.425 --> 04:19.040
[MOANS THEN GASPS]

04:19.844 --> 04:21.960
Mm. Mm. Mm-hm.

04:22.221 --> 04:23.586
Oh.

04:23.806 --> 04:25.797
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

06:00.069 --> 06:02.060
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

06:02.404 --> 06:06.067
KENYA: Sheriff, you think that we fan out
like we did last night, continue canvassing?

06:06.283 --> 06:08.945
WOMAN 1: Dumb girl who brought this here,
and she's gonna save us?

06:09.161 --> 06:11.618
MAN 1: Fucking mess.
WOMAN Z: Fucking danger hole.

06:11.830 --> 06:12.990
MAN 2:
No way out of this one.

06:13.207 --> 06:17.291
How many there gotta be in this state?
We don't have the time to figure it out.

06:17.503 --> 06:19.789
-There's gotta be a lot of them.
-The truth is...

06:20.005 --> 06:22.212
...I don't know how to narrow the search.

06:22.424 --> 06:23.755
I do.

06:25.469 --> 06:27.676
I found the dead girl in the woods last night.

06:27.888 --> 06:32.222
And I didn't recognize her, just like I didn't
recognize a single one of those vampires.

06:32.434 --> 06:35.471
What if they came from another town
that was hitjust like ours...

06:35.688 --> 06:38.725
-...and brought the girl with them?
-You saying we ID this girl...

06:38.941 --> 06:40.477
...find out where they were last?

06:40.693 --> 06:45.608
Maybe those folks can tell us who it is
we're dealing with and where they're holed up.

06:47.157 --> 06:48.442
What do you think, boss?

06:48.659 --> 06:49.865
I think it's a long shot.

06:50.077 --> 06:52.739
But like you said,
we're spread pretty thin right now.

06:52.955 --> 06:53.990
Where are the feds?

06:54.206 --> 06:57.949
I've been making calls, haven't gotten
an answer. We're fending for ourselves.

06:58.168 --> 06:59.999
Where did you say this body was?

07:00.212 --> 07:03.079
Quarter mile away.
Just down Antelope Road.

07:04.049 --> 07:05.255
-All right, then.
SAM: Yeah.

07:05.467 --> 07:06.627
I gotta get Adilyn home.

07:06.844 --> 07:09.506
Sookie and Alcide,
meet Jason and me at the station.

07:09.722 --> 07:11.713
-Kenya will drop you off.
KENYA: Oh, no, sheriff--

07:11.932 --> 07:14.639
I do not wanna hear it today.
Not today, Kenya.

07:14.852 --> 07:17.514
-Somebody's gotta be there.
-Mr. Mayor. Uh....

07:17.730 --> 07:19.971
Now, I know we discussed
protocol for tonight...

07:20.190 --> 07:23.398
...but folks are asking what they gonna do
with themselves today.

07:23.611 --> 07:26.148
I told them my door's open
for prayer and council...

07:26.363 --> 07:30.276
...but it sure would be nice
if they had something to keep them occupied.

07:31.118 --> 07:34.736
Yeah, okay. Okay, yeah. Yeah. Yeah.

07:39.126 --> 07:40.787
Listen up, y'all. Uh--

07:41.003 --> 07:45.121
You know, today is a dark day.

07:45.341 --> 07:48.959
There's no manual on how to get through this,
believe me, I know.

07:49.178 --> 07:54.013
But I think keeping busy
and being of service...

07:54.183 --> 07:55.719
...is as good a way to go as any.

07:56.352 --> 07:59.970
One thing I do know for sure,
when we get Arlene back...

08:00.189 --> 08:04.933
...and we will get her back, she's gonna be
none too pleased with the state of Bellefleur's.

08:05.152 --> 08:08.940
So it sure would be nice
to put it back together for her.

08:09.156 --> 08:10.987
Ain't it risky going back there?

08:11.325 --> 08:13.657
Remember, as long as it's daylight,
you'll be safe.

08:13.869 --> 08:17.953
But again, I strongly recommend
y'all be in your houses by sundown.

08:18.832 --> 08:23.451
And do not even think of leaving,
unless accompanied by a vampire.

08:23.879 --> 08:25.210
[PEOPLE MURMURING]

08:30.010 --> 08:34.174
-l was thinking of checking in on Lafayette.
-He didn't make it in this morning, did he?

08:34.390 --> 08:38.178
No, sir. And with the way his side
of the family can go to dark places...

08:38.394 --> 08:39.930
...it worries me. It do.

08:40.145 --> 08:43.182
-How about | go along with you?
-No. You got your hands full here.

08:43.399 --> 08:46.766
And like the mayor said,
it'll do me good being of service.

08:46.985 --> 08:48.316
Lafayette needs me.

08:49.029 --> 08:50.610
I'm all he's got left.

08:51.115 --> 08:52.605
All right, honey, all right.

08:54.201 --> 08:57.238
ANDY: Let's go, Adilyn.
-How come I can't come with you?

08:57.454 --> 09:00.161
Because, darling, a crime scene
ain't no place for a child.

09:00.374 --> 09:02.740
-Well, I'm 18.
-I know you are, but not really.

09:02.960 --> 09:05.246
-l'm taking you home.
-What about Rocky and Wade?

09:05.462 --> 09:09.296
Don't you think that I should stay with them?
I mean, isn't that what family does?

09:09.508 --> 09:11.544
Stick together at a time like this.

09:15.264 --> 09:17.880
All right, but I want you home
a solid hour before dark.

09:18.100 --> 09:20.591
-Okay, Daddy.
-All the same rules as last night apply.

09:20.811 --> 09:25.100
You hear? lf Jessica comes back,
you do not invite her in.

09:25.315 --> 09:26.851
-Of course.
-You got that?

09:29.528 --> 09:30.563
All right.

09:33.449 --> 09:35.440
[LOUD THUDS AND
VAMPIRES SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

09:35.659 --> 09:37.650
[WHIMPERING]

09:40.414 --> 09:43.076
-Did you hear that?
-Yeah.

09:43.709 --> 09:45.540
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

09:46.211 --> 09:49.874
Jesus fuck. How could you,
you fucking cunt?

09:50.090 --> 09:52.502
-It just happened.
TROY: That's your fucking excuse?

09:52.718 --> 09:56.882
So when l rip your fucking head off, you
won't mind ifl use that one, will you, mate?

09:57.097 --> 10:00.180
I told you l was so fucking hungry
I just lost control.

10:00.392 --> 10:05.261
We're all hungry, Ronnie,
that's why we put the fucking plan in place.

10:05.481 --> 10:08.439
We share or we starve.

10:08.650 --> 10:09.901
Do you understand?

10:10.110 --> 10:11.941
Yeah, I understand.

10:12.362 --> 10:14.273
-It won't happen again.
JEROME: NO, it can't.

10:14.490 --> 10:17.527
Because you cut our rations down
by a fourth.

10:17.743 --> 10:20.826
Fuck! Now we're gonna have to go
back out hunting again.

10:21.038 --> 10:23.029
What? No. No, no, no. Not again.

10:23.248 --> 10:26.706
We have no choice. Last night should've
brought in three times the bodies.

10:26.919 --> 10:29.581
-Great choice on that town.
-How was I supposed to know...

10:29.797 --> 10:31.833
...they'd invite vampires to their barbeque?

10:32.049 --> 10:34.882
And if you're so tired,
why don't you take a nice, long nap...

10:35.093 --> 10:36.799
...and spare us your endless whining?

10:37.012 --> 10:39.094
You have some nerve after what you just did.

10:39.306 --> 10:41.888
All right, everyone, just shut the fuck up!

10:42.434 --> 10:44.595
Look, we can't keep losing our shit like this.

10:45.187 --> 10:48.099
If we do, we die.

10:48.315 --> 10:50.101
We're all gonna die, no matter what.

10:50.317 --> 10:53.901
But it doesn't have to be like this.
We don't have to die like animals.

10:54.530 --> 10:56.270
Betty, you were a teacher, right?

10:57.115 --> 10:58.150
Yes.

10:59.034 --> 11:02.618
You gotta have a whole hell of a lot
of self-control to be a teacher.

11:04.998 --> 11:06.829
Good. New plan.

11:07.042 --> 11:08.998
Betty, you gonna be the new reaper.

11:09.211 --> 11:13.170
-Ronnie, you're on sleep patrol from now on.
-What? How can we trust him to wake us?

11:13.382 --> 11:16.795
Because he's gonna eat last
until he can prove he can be trusted.

11:17.010 --> 11:19.171
-That ain't fair--
-Tough shit, you little bitch.

11:19.388 --> 11:21.754
JEROME: Betty.
BETTY: Fine.

11:22.140 --> 11:23.266
l'll reap.

11:23.475 --> 11:26.262
But can we please stop acting like savages?

11:26.812 --> 11:28.643
Just go get us some fucking food.

11:29.815 --> 11:30.895
GO.

11:34.361 --> 11:36.352
[WOMEN WHIMPERING]

11:42.661 --> 11:43.696
[GASPS]

11:49.334 --> 11:50.494
BELINDA:
Jesus Christ.

11:50.836 --> 11:53.498
No, please! NO! No! No, please--

11:53.714 --> 11:56.956
[SCREAMING]

12:03.015 --> 12:05.256
-Oh, my God.
-Oh, I know.

12:05.475 --> 12:08.217
-My heart's beating out of my chest.
ARLENE: NO, I know her.

12:08.437 --> 12:11.474
-I know I know her. ljust don't know how.
NICOLE: Aah!

12:11.690 --> 12:13.146
-Aah!
-What is it, sweetie?

12:13.317 --> 12:14.978
It's cramping or something.

12:15.193 --> 12:16.694
Why is she cramping?

12:16.904 --> 12:19.941
-It's digging into her.
-Okay. Okay, let me see what I can do.

12:20.157 --> 12:24.400
-Somebody told me I'd die sober in a bar.
-Listen to me, Jane, you're not gonna die here.

12:24.620 --> 12:27.612
We're gonna get you through this.
You're detoxing, that's all.

12:27.831 --> 12:31.289
Holly, did Rocky and Wade have Miss Harris
for fourth grade?

12:31.668 --> 12:35.581
Miss Harris? Yeah. Yeah. She was the only
teacher who ever said that they were smart.

12:35.797 --> 12:38.083
I didn't believe her, but I appreciated it.

12:38.300 --> 12:39.881
-Was her first name Betty?
-Uh....

12:40.260 --> 12:42.842
Yeah. Yeah, I think it was.

12:43.055 --> 12:45.171
-What, why?
-That was her.

12:45.390 --> 12:49.429
-That lady. We know her. She taught our kids.
-The reaper?

12:49.645 --> 12:52.307
Well, I was too scared to even look.
Are you sure?

12:52.522 --> 12:55.480
Yeah. Uh-huh. And she recognized me too.

12:55.692 --> 12:59.651
She was gonna pick me and then she saw me
and she took Belinda instead.

12:59.863 --> 13:01.854
She spared me.

13:02.074 --> 13:04.156
I think she might be our way out of here.

13:04.368 --> 13:06.074
-How?
-I don't know.

13:06.286 --> 13:09.824
But I gotta believe Miss Harris
doesn't have it in her to eat us.

13:09.998 --> 13:12.284
[COUGHING]

13:12.459 --> 13:14.040
[G RU NTS]

13:16.088 --> 13:20.752
-| wish I shared your optimism.
-Okay, listen to me, y'all.

13:20.968 --> 13:23.050
I know I've had some pretty shitty luck...

13:23.261 --> 13:27.300
...and it probably ain't too reassuring to be
in a situation this fucked up with me...

13:27.516 --> 13:29.598
...but that is why you've gotta believe me...

13:29.810 --> 13:32.847
...when I tell you
that I did not survive four lousy husbands...

13:33.063 --> 13:37.523
...a serial-killer boyfriend
and the sort of suicide of my love, Terry...

13:37.734 --> 13:41.773
...to die in a dingy basement
of a fucking vampire bar.

13:41.989 --> 13:46.107
I am getting us out of here. Do you hear me?

13:48.537 --> 13:50.198
ANDY:
You sure this was the place?

13:53.250 --> 13:54.990
There she is.

13:58.672 --> 14:00.708
JASON:
Oh, shit.

14:00.882 --> 14:02.338
[FLIES BUZZING]

14:02.509 --> 14:04.090
Right.

14:07.681 --> 14:08.966
Animals got to her.

14:09.182 --> 14:12.515
I hate to be morbid,
but do you think she's got any fingerprints left?

14:15.022 --> 14:17.104
JASON:
No, it's not necessary.

14:17.315 --> 14:20.603
Sometimes not being clever
makes you a better detective.

14:21.403 --> 14:22.813
This is a Starbucks card.

14:29.036 --> 14:33.029
"Mary Beth Grant," 25 years old,
from Saint Alice.

14:33.749 --> 14:35.740
Saint Alice? That's only two towns over.

14:35.959 --> 14:39.372
Mayor Rampeaux gave me a call last week,
never called him back.

14:39.796 --> 14:41.752
I'll try their sheriff.

14:42.049 --> 14:43.664
[KEYPAD BEEPING]

14:49.264 --> 14:50.925
Sook, you Okay?

14:51.683 --> 14:56.097
There's a quote on one of the gravestones
in the cemetery.

14:56.313 --> 14:59.055
"The brutal indifference of life."

14:59.441 --> 15:01.272
That's true.

15:02.027 --> 15:05.815
Life don't care how old you are
or where you're from.

15:06.615 --> 15:08.981
Or how good a person you've been.

15:09.785 --> 15:11.025
Totally indifferent.

15:11.578 --> 15:15.070
Sook, stop looking. It won't do you no good.

15:15.290 --> 15:16.905
Voicemail box is full.

15:17.125 --> 15:18.706
It just rang and rang.

15:18.919 --> 15:22.537
Well, I guess we're taking
a road trip to Saint Alice.

15:24.424 --> 15:26.255
We'll go door-to-door if we have to.

15:33.600 --> 15:35.761
SOOKIE:
Come on, y'all, let's go.

15:36.812 --> 15:38.803
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

15:40.982 --> 15:43.644
I heard you.

15:47.739 --> 15:49.195
[LAFAYETTE SIGHS]

15:50.826 --> 15:53.283
I know I may not be
who you wanna see right now...

15:54.162 --> 15:56.323
...but I came to check on you all the same.

15:56.540 --> 15:58.201
See how you're holding up.

15:58.416 --> 16:00.543
I'm holding up all right.

16:04.798 --> 16:06.709
How you holding up?

16:06.925 --> 16:11.089
I lost her a long time ago. I deserve to just--

16:13.348 --> 16:19.890
But then last night--
Lord, your timing is something to behold.

16:21.022 --> 16:23.434
Last night, Tara and me made good.

16:24.442 --> 16:25.818
Just before that evil came...

16:26.027 --> 16:30.316
...I said my peace and I took care of my baby
the way I always was meant to do.

16:31.241 --> 16:35.405
I'm not a big fan of Jesus' work, but that's
some pretty epic fucking timing, Auntie.

16:35.620 --> 16:39.738
Problem is, I'm glad I had that with Tara,
but it ain't enough.

16:39.958 --> 16:40.993
I want more.

16:41.585 --> 16:44.827
I wanna wrap my arms around her,
hold on to her.

16:45.046 --> 16:48.038
IgetH,ldo,
but you can't hold on to her, Auntie.

16:48.258 --> 16:51.546
-Trust me, I tried.
-That's where you're wrong, Lafayette.

16:51.761 --> 16:53.717
Tara came back to me last night.

16:53.930 --> 16:57.297
Just after her body left,
her spirit returned to me.

16:57.517 --> 17:00.884
See, she needs my help
before heading up to heaven.

17:01.104 --> 17:02.640
Which is why I need your help.

17:02.856 --> 17:06.098
Why do you need my--? Oh, no, no, no.

17:06.318 --> 17:08.934
I'm not summoning Tara.
I don't do that bullshit no more.

17:09.154 --> 17:11.566
You don't gotta do nothing.
All I need is some blood.

17:11.781 --> 17:14.363
-The rest is in God's hands.
-What? What blood?

17:16.953 --> 17:20.070
I don't even like the taste of V,
but when I got it in me...

17:20.290 --> 17:21.700
...I am with her.

17:21.917 --> 17:25.080
Well, Iookie-Iookie at you.
I saw you taking a little blood last night.

17:25.295 --> 17:28.537
-Auntie, that's not Tara, that's the V.
-You are wrong.

17:28.757 --> 17:30.622
It most definitely was Tara.

17:30.842 --> 17:34.551
Well, it most definitely was Gandhi
I was playing Chinese checkers with...

17:34.763 --> 17:36.344
...that time in the bathtub.

17:36.556 --> 17:37.716
You're making fun of me?

17:37.933 --> 17:41.266
My little girl is stuck between heaven and Earth,
and that's what you do?

17:41.478 --> 17:44.185
-She needs me.
-She don't need nobody, Auntie, Tara's dead.

17:44.648 --> 17:45.808
She gone.

17:46.024 --> 17:47.980
And she'd want you to let her go.

17:48.193 --> 17:53.062
-And not go down this path again.
-You turned my Tara into a vampire.

17:53.281 --> 17:55.442
And then you don't let me
have a second chance?

17:55.700 --> 17:57.736
You're a selfish, two-faced, no-good sinner.

17:57.953 --> 18:01.036
And you a drug addict, you trifling bitch,
through and through.

18:01.248 --> 18:03.910
-You're going to hell!
-That's what this is.

18:09.673 --> 18:11.664
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

18:34.489 --> 18:35.524
[GAGS]

18:36.199 --> 18:37.234
Are you okay?

18:41.204 --> 18:44.037
You know, my daddy's following
a lead in the woods right now.

18:44.249 --> 18:46.740
And I bet you anything
he's bringing Holly back today.

18:56.720 --> 19:02.431
So you all really are sweeping up
like your mayor told you to.

19:02.642 --> 19:05.679
-Seems like the right thing to do.
-Why?

19:05.895 --> 19:07.055
Got a better idea?

19:07.689 --> 19:10.431
Merlotte's gone. I saw him drive off
with my own two eyes...

19:10.650 --> 19:14.484
...so yeah, there's probably better ideas
than being his janitor.

19:14.696 --> 19:17.529
Right now there ain't nothing to do,
but be good citizens.

19:17.741 --> 19:19.823
And let our law enforcers do theirjob.

19:20.035 --> 19:22.947
And what job is that exactly?
The job of protecting us?

19:23.163 --> 19:24.994
Like they did last night?

19:25.206 --> 19:27.242
[MAXINE SCREAMS]

19:27.500 --> 19:29.536
Jesus.

19:30.462 --> 19:31.827
MAN 1:
What happened? What happened?

19:33.548 --> 19:34.879
What are they doing there?

19:35.091 --> 19:38.049
The vampers are keeping them fresh
for when they come back.

19:38.261 --> 19:41.298
-I thought they only drank live bodies.
-I don't fucking know.

19:41.514 --> 19:43.926
-You think they're coming back?
KAREN: What's to stop them?

19:44.142 --> 19:46.053
They saw how ill-equipped we were.

19:46.269 --> 19:49.807
-And our law enforcers are on a field trip.
-Hey, they'll be back by sundown.

19:50.023 --> 19:52.935
-Andy told me himself.
-And what about Sam Merlotte?

19:53.151 --> 19:54.186
What about him?

19:54.402 --> 19:58.441
You all remember how he ran his campaign
on "I'm a politician you can trust."

19:58.656 --> 20:01.068
Last night when we was
bringing folks in here...

20:01.284 --> 20:04.742
-...I looked out the window and saw a dog.
MAN 2: So what?

20:04.954 --> 20:05.989
So?

20:06.206 --> 20:08.367
So that dog turned into our mayor.

20:08.583 --> 20:10.198
-What?
WOMAN: What?

20:10.377 --> 20:13.210
I'll be damned. I knew it.

20:13.421 --> 20:16.003
And all this time I was blaming the NyQuil.

20:16.216 --> 20:20.050
About a year ago, I saw a bear
going through my trash out back.

20:20.261 --> 20:24.300
And by the time I got Hoyt's BB gun,
the bear was gone...

20:24.516 --> 20:29.977
...but standing right there in its place,
Sam Merlotte, in his birthday suit.

20:30.188 --> 20:32.770
-Didn't you vote for Sam for mayor?
-I did.

20:32.982 --> 20:34.893
-Why?
-Well, I don't know.

20:35.110 --> 20:37.943
There's a bigger picture here
y'all are missing.

20:38.154 --> 20:42.272
This town's full of vampers,
has a dog for a mayor...

20:42.492 --> 20:46.201
